remarks: Real number less-than is weakly linear.  Axiom for real and complex numbers, derived from set theory.  This construction-dependent theorem should not be referenced directly; instead, use ~ ax-pre-ltwlin . (Contributed by Jim Kingdon, 12-Jan-2020.) (New usage is discouraged.)
statement: axpre-ltwlin $p |- ( ( A e. RR /\ B e. RR /\ C e. RR ) -> ( A <RR B -> ( A <RR C \/ C <RR B ) ) ) $.
